story.title: The Intruder - Episode 1
story.storyDescription: After a strange man knocks on the door, Eddie lands in a terrifying alternate reality where he learns an amazing secret about his father.
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: Jonathan Rosen is a transplanted New Yorker, who now lives with his family in sunny, South Florida. He's been writing ever since he was a little kid, but it's much more legible now.

story.prePaywallNotification: The guy at Eddie’s door is not from this world – and he’s deadly. Read more of THE INTRUDER.
story.postPaywallNotification: Where did Eddie go?! The answer will surprise you. Read the next episode of THE INTRUDER.

messages.text: There’s someone knocking at the door for you.
Who?
I don’t know. Some guy.
Don’t answer! Just stay away from the door.
Too late for that.
I didn’t open the door, but I already told him you weren’t home.
I shouted at him through the window on top.
What did he say?
He said he didn’t believe me. He’s still knocking. Hard.
What does this guy look like?
He looks young. Maybe in his twenties? I don’t know. Thin guy. Has a beard.
A beard? How long?
Not long. Trimmed.
Does he have on a leather jacket?
Let me look.
Never mind. Stay away from the door. I’m coming home.
Yeah, he’s got a leather jacket. It’s long. Like past his knees.
Crap! He saw me looking.
I told you to stay away!
It’s too late now!
Listen to me carefully: Stay away from the door, I mean it!
I’m already on my way.
You’re like forty minutes away!
I’m coming. Just stay away from him.
Okay, but you’re worrying me now.
Should I call the police?
NO! I don’t want the police involved in this. I said I’m on my way.
You don’t want the police involved? Involved in what?
Who is this guy?
It’s too long to explain now. But keep away from the door!
Dad? He’s BANGING on the door now.
Dammit. Get upstairs. Go to my room.
Upstairs? Why??
Does this guy have a gun?
No, he doesn’t like guns. He uses hatchets.
HATCHETS?? Are you kidding me? Is this guy some deranged axe murderer??
No, he’s much worse than that.
I’m calling your phone. I need to hear your voice.
NO! Don’t call. I don’t want him to hear where you are.
Keep your phone on silent and I’ll tell you what to do.
Keep calm. It’ll be okay. I promise.
Keep calm??
How can I keep calm when there’s some crazy hatchet killer at the door?
Go upstairs now. Walk quietly on the steps.
No. I’m going to run out the back door.
No! Don’t do that!  He’ll catch you!
I already told you. GO UPSTAIRS NOW!
He’ll catch me? Who is he??
Just get upstairs!!
Dad! It sounds like he’s THROWING his body against the door!
Are you in my room yet?
Yes. You’re right, I feel so much safer now.
I know you’re scared, but keep calm and listen to me very carefully.
Holy crap! I hear the door cracking! WHO IS THIS GUY??
Someone I knew from a long time ago. I’ll tell you about it later.
For right now, I want you to go into my closet.
Seriously? You want me to hide in your closet?? That’s your plan?
You didn’t let me finish. Go into my closet. Don’t panic, but do it quickly.
Okay, hang on.
one minute later
Are you in my closet?
Yes! What do you want me to do?
Go to the back.
Okay.
OMG! You have a leather jacket like his. Why did I never see this??
I’m not talking about the leather jacket now.
I never saw you wearing this in my life!
Push the jacket out of the way.
Behind it is a small box. Do you see it?
Yeah. And?
Take it and open it. There should be two things in there.
Okay…
What is this?
Which one are you holding?
I don’t know, it’s like a necklace.
Okay, good. And the other should be the amulet.
DAD! I heard the door crack! HE’S IN THE HOUSE!!
Put on the necklace!
What good is a necklace going to do??
Put it on NOW!!!
Okay, it’s on. What now?
Get out of there, but be very quiet.
Not a sound. Don’t even breathe loudly.
Make sure your phone is on silent.
What’s going on? Why am I doing this?
Is it on silent?
Yes.
Okay, you’re invisible now. Anything that’s in contact with your skin will also be invisible.
WHAT??
I’m serious. Only you can see yourself. Your hands, whatever you’re holding.
But if you look in the mirror, you won’t see anything.
HOLY CRAP!! I just looked in the dresser mirror. You’re right!
I know I’m right! Just stay quiet and find somewhere to hide.
Don’t be in the same space as him for too long, or he’ll detect you.
This is crazy!!
OMG, he’s here!
He’s in the same room!!
Keep quiet!! He can’t see you. If necessary put on the amulet, but only as a last resort.
Crap! I left the amulet in the closet!
Where are you now??
I’m in the hallway outside your room.
But he’s in your room!!
He’s talking to me. Saying he knows I’m close by.
Wait. He’s coming out.
He just walked by me, like really right by me. He’s going to MY room.
Go get that amulet!!
Okay, I got it. What now?
Crap! He heard me come back in!! He’s back in the room!!
Dad, he’s talking to me! He’s right outside the closet!! What do I do??
ATTACH THE AMULET TO THE NECKLACE!! NOW! NOW! NOW!!
Eddie?
EDDIE??
